<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-40-0880 </DOCNO><TEXT>Several liver function tests using the oral application of a nitrogencompound labelled with /sup 15/N and the subsequent determination of/sup 15/N in a certain fraction of urine by emission spectrometry aredescribed. Because of the key position of the liver in the metabolismof nitrogen compounds the results of these tests allow conclusions concerningdisturbances of special liver functions. Instructions for the clinicaluse of the '[/sup 15/N]Ammonium Test', '[/sup 15/N]Hippurate Test' the'[/sup 15/N]Methacetin Test', and the '[/sup 15/N]Glycine Test' are given.</TEXT></DOC>